1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
We built Ailurus for creators who want to own their audience and their payout path.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Centralized platforms take large cuts, control your files, and can remove you overnight.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Web3 alternatives ask fans for wallets, gas fees, and seed phrases — not mainstream ready.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Ailurus fixes this with Google login, USDC subscriptions, Walrus storage, and Seal paywalls.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Landing page — publish privately and get paid globally.

6
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Scroll — creators keep USDC revenue; fans never see gas or WAL tokens.

7
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Tap "View live demo" to enter the product on Sui Testnet.

8
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Feed — browse posts from on-chain creators in a familiar social layout.

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Not a wallet dashboard — it feels like Instagram or Threads.

10
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Open Explore to discover creator profiles.

11
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Discover creators registered through our Move contract on Sui.

12
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Each profile shows price, posts, and subscriber-only encrypted drops.

13
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Subscriber-only content stays locked until a fan pays in USDC.

14
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Tap Subscribe — the Move contract records subscription state on chain.

15
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:08,000
USDC settles to the creator; Enoki sponsors all SUI gas fees.

16
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Back to Feed — exclusive albums unlock instantly.

17
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Seal decrypts media only for active subscribers.

18
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Behind the UI: encrypted bytes live on Walrus; Seal enforces access policy.

19
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Creators upload via Walrus SDK — Cetus swaps USDC to WAL for storage fees.

20
00:02:52,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Our Cloudflare worker sponsors gas through Enoki with an allowlisted Move target list.

21
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Identity, settlement, storage, and privacy — one product path on Sui Testnet.

22
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:18,000
In summary: Ailurus is a Web2-grade creator subscription layer on the full Sui stack.

23
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Repo is public, contracts are live on Testnet, Mainnet target: July 2026.

24
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Next: Enoki production config, creator onboarding, and analytics. Thank you.
